SMART FLOOR CLEANER ROBOT – RESULTS AND OUTCOMES

PROJECT RESULTS

1. The Smart Floor Cleaner robot was successfully designed and implemented using embedded system components.

2. The robot was able to move autonomously in different directions including forward, backward, left,
and right movement.

3. The HC-SR04 ultrasonic sensor successfully detected obstacles in real time and enabled collision avoidance.

4. The Arduino Uno microcontroller accurately processed sensor data and controlled the 
motor driver module for robot navigation.

5. The L298N motor driver successfully controlled the speed and direction of the DC motors.

6. The cleaning mechanism operated continuously during robot movement and demonstrated basic floor-cleaning
functionality.

7. The rechargeable battery provided stable power supply for portable robot operation.

8. The system successfully reduced manual effort and cleaning time in small indoor environments.

9. The project demonstrated the practical implementation of embedded systems, robotics automation, 
sensor interfacing, and motor control.

10. The prototype operated as a low-cost autonomous robotic cleaning solution suitable for educational and 
automation-based applications.


PERFORMANCE OBSERVATIONS

- Obstacle detection response was accurate within the sensor operating range.
- The robot movement was stable on flat surfaces.
- Battery backup supported continuous operation for a limited duration.
- Motor response was successfully controlled through programmed logic.

